  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Project Manager/Project Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead and manage multiple projects simultaneously, defining project scope, goals, and deliverables</li><li>Develop comprehensive project plans and monitor progress, adjusting as necessary to ensure successful completion</li><li>Coordinate and allocate resources effectively across various project stages</li><li>Conduct regular project status meetings and provide timely updates to stakeholders</li><li>Identify and mitigate potential risks that may impact project timelines or outcomes</li><li>Manage project budgets, ensuring cost-effectiveness and adherence to financial guidelines</li><li>Foster strong relationships with clients, team members, and other stakeholders</li><li>Implement and maintain project management best practices and methodologies</li><li>Mentor and guide project team members, promoting a collaborative and high-performance environment</li><li>Ensure project deliverables meet or exceed quality standards and client expectations</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Preferred candidates should preferably possess the following:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor's degree/Diploma in Business Administration, Architectural, Engineering, or a related field</li><li>Minimum of 3 years of project management experience in Interior Architectural projects and building projects</li><li>Proven track record of successfully delivering complex projects on time and within budget</li><li>Strong leadership skills with the ability to motivate and guide cross-functional teams</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to interact effectively with stakeholders at all levels</li></ul>",
